USER RESPONSIBILITIES
---------------------
It is the sole responsibility of end users to respect websites' policies when
using Pillar's crawling features. Users are advised to adhere to applicable
privacy policies and terms of use of websites prior to initiating any scraping
activities. By default, Pillar (via FireCrawl) respects the directives specified
in websites' robots.txt files when crawling.

By utilizing Pillar, you expressly agree to comply with these conditions.
